## Managing Users & Groups

```bash
# Create a user
aws iam create-user --user-name joon-dev

# Create access keys for a user (for CLI use)
aws iam create-access-key --user-name joon-dev
# Store the SecretAccessKey — it is only shown once

# Create a group and add user
aws iam create-group --group-name developers
aws iam add-user-to-group --group-name developers --user-name joon-dev

# Attach a managed policy to a group
aws iam attach-group-policy \
  --group-name developers \
  --policy-arn arn:aws:iam::aws:policy/ReadOnlyAccess

# List users and their groups
aws iam list-users --query 'Users[*].[UserName,CreateDate]' --output table
aws iam list-groups-for-user --user-name joon-dev

# Delete access key (rotate credentials)
aws iam list-access-keys --user-name joon-dev
aws iam delete-access-key \
  --user-name joon-dev \
  --access-key-id AKIAXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX
```

