## Key Insight for DevOps

Never use your root account for anything except billing. Create an admin IAM user on day one, enable MFA on both root and admin, then never touch root again.

Never put access keys directly on EC2 instances, in code, or in environment variables if you can use an instance role instead. Credentials in code get committed to git. Credentials on instances get leaked via SSRF vulnerabilities. Roles have no long-term secret to steal.

The first sign of a breach in many AWS accounts is unexpected API calls in CloudTrail. Enable CloudTrail in every region, every account, from day one.